#compdef lapdev-cli lapdev-ws lapdev-guest-agent lapdev-kube-manager
# ============================================================================
# _lapdev-cli — zsh completion for **lapdev-cli** + **lapdev-ws** +
#            **lapdev-guest-agent** + **lapdev-kube-manager** —
#            lapce/lapdev, the **self-hosted remote development
#            environment platform** by the Lapce team (the Rust IDE
#            built on the floem GUI framework).  Structurally the
#            open-source self-hosted alternative to **Gitpod** /
#            **GitHub Codespaces** / **Coder** / **Daytona** /
#            **DevPod** — runs as a Kubernetes-deployed control
#            plane (the `lapdev-ws` workspace daemon + the
#            `lapdev-kube-manager` Kubernetes manager + the
#            `lapdev-guest-agent` per-workspace guest agent) that
#            provisions developer dev-containers from `.devcontainer/
#            devcontainer.json` specs on demand, and the
#            `lapdev-cli` is the local-machine CLI that
#            authenticates against the Lapdev API + opens SSH
#            connections to the running dev-containers + establishes
#            port-forwarding tunnels for the developer's local IDE.
#            SSH transport is **russh** — the canonical pure-Rust
#            SSH 2.0 implementation by Pierre-Étienne Meunier
#            (originally the SSH layer of the Pijul VCS, later
#            extracted into the stand-alone `russh` crate that
#            powers essentially every modern Rust SSH-aware tool).
#            Rust=182 **OPENS** Axis 127 (pure-Rust SSH 2.0 protocol
#            implementation / **russh** ecosystem — `russh` +
#            `russh-keys` + `russh-sftp` + `russh-cryptovec` +
#            `russh-config` + the typed `Auth` / `ChannelMsg` /
#            `Session` / `Handler` primitives) at 1/0/0.
# ============================================================================
#
