# WHAT IT IS
#   Lapdev is the **self-hosted remote-development-environment
#   platform** for engineering teams that want Codespaces-grade
#   ephemeral dev containers without sending their source code
#   to Microsoft, and without paying $0.30+/hour per developer
#   for managed-service alternatives.  Architecture:
#
#     • **`lapdev-cli`** (local laptop)
#         The developer's local-machine entry point.
#         Authenticates against the Lapdev API server via OAuth
#         (token stored in OS keychain via the typed `keyring`
#         crate);  opens SSH connections to running workspaces
#         via russh's typed `Session` + `Handler` primitives;
#         establishes typed port-forwarding tunnels so VS Code /
#         Cursor / Lapce / Zed / Neovim Remote can connect to
#         the dev-container's language servers.
#     • **`lapdev-ws`** (server VM / pod)
#         The workspace daemon that runs inside each provisioned
#         dev-container.  Listens on an SSH port (russh server-
#         side typed `russh::server::Handler` impl), accepts
#         developer SSH connections, and exposes the
#         container's filesystem + processes via the typed
#         tarpc RPC mesh to the conductor.
#     • **`lapdev-guest-agent`** (per-workspace in-container
#         supervisor) Manages the lifecycle of language servers,
#         file watchers, devcontainer features, port-forwarding
#         declarations, and live-share sessions inside the
#         dev-container.
#     • **`lapdev-kube-manager`** (cluster control plane)
#         The Kubernetes manager component.  Watches the typed
#         `Workspace` CRD via kube-rs, materializes typed Pod +
#         PersistentVolumeClaim + Service + Ingress + NetworkPolicy
#         resources for each workspace, applies typed RBAC scopes,
#         handles cleanup-on-idle, and serves typed control-plane
#         RPCs to the conductor.
#
#   The `lapdev-cli` (the primary developer-facing binary) has
#   the simplest interface — just a few high-level subcommands
#   for authentication + workspace SSH-tunnel lifecycle:
#
#     • lapdev login [--device-name <NAME>] [--api-host <HOST>]
#                                     Browser-based OAuth flow,
#                                     stores token in OS
#                                     keychain
#     • lapdev logout [--api-host <HOST>]
#                                     Delete token from keychain
#     • lapdev whoami [--api-host <HOST>]
#                                     Print authenticated user
#                                     info
#     • lapdev devbox connect
#                  [--api-host <HOST>] Connect to a Lapdev
#                                     devbox + establish port
#                                     forwarding tunnels
#                                     (the actual russh-backed
#                                     SSH connection step)
#
#     Global flags:
#       -v, --verbose                 enable verbose logging
#       --log-dir <PATH>              directory for lapdev-cli
#                                     log files
#                                     (env: LAPDEV_LOG_DIR;
#                                     defaults to OS-native
#                                     conventional path:
#                                     `~/Library/Logs/Lapdev`
#                                     on macOS,
#                                     `$XDG_STATE_HOME/lapdev/
#                                     logs` on Linux,
#                                     `%LOCALAPPDATA%/Lapdev/
#                                     logs` on Windows)
#       --api-host                    Lapdev API host
#                                     (alias `--api-url`,
#                                     env: LAPDEV_API_HOST,
#                                     e.g. `app.lap.dev`)
#       -h, --help                    Show help
#       -V, --version                 Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `lapce/lapdev`'s workspace `Cargo.toml` declares a **direct**
#   dependency on `russh = { version = "0.53.0" }`.  The
#   `crates/proxy-ssh/` workspace member implements the typed
#   server-side `russh::server::Server` trait, registering
#   typed `Handler` impls for the auth + channel-open + data +
#   eof + close lifecycle events;  the typed
#   `crates/cli/src/devbox/commands/connect.rs` implements the
#   client-side `russh::client::Handler` trait + uses typed
#   `russh::client::connect_stream()` to dial the workspace's
#   SSH endpoint over a custom typed TCP-tunneled transport.
#
#   **russh** (`russh` crate;  forked from `thrussh` in 2022 by
#   the Eugene Hauptmann-led successor maintainer team after
#   Pierre-Étienne Meunier moved focus back to the Pijul VCS)
#   is **THE canonical pure-Rust SSH 2.0 implementation** —
#   reference implementation of the IETF SSH-2 protocol
#   (RFC 4250 + RFC 4251 + RFC 4252 + RFC 4253 + RFC 4254 +
#   RFC 4256 + RFC 4419 + RFC 4716 + RFC 5656 + RFC 8268 +
#   RFC 8308 + RFC 8332 + RFC 8709 + RFC 8731 + RFC 9142 +
#   RFC 9579) in idiomatic safe-Rust with the explicit goal of
#   replacing OpenSSH (the dominant C reference implementation)
#   for Rust consumers that need embedded SSH server / client
#   capabilities.  In active development since 2017, with
#   1,000+ ★ on github.com/Eugeny/russh.  The project is
#   sponsored by Eugene Hauptmann (the author of **warpdotdev**
#   /**warp.dev** the AI-powered terminal, and **Tabby** the
#   open-source terminal that uses russh as its SSH transport).
#
#   russh ships:
#
#     • Typed `russh::client::Handler`
#       Typed `russh::client::Session`
#       Typed `russh::client::Config`
#       Typed `russh::client::Handle`
#                                      client-side typed
#                                      session + channel
#                                      management
#     • Typed `russh::server::Handler`
#       Typed `russh::server::Session`
#       Typed `russh::server::Config`
#       Typed `russh::server::Server`
#                                      server-side typed
#                                      auth + channel + global-
#                                      request handlers
#     • Typed `russh::client::connect`
#       Typed `russh::client::connect_stream`
#       Typed `russh::server::run_on_socket`
#                                      typed connection
#                                      constructors
#     • Typed `russh::ChannelMsg`      typed enum: Data,
#                                      ExtendedData, Eof,
#                                      Close, XonXoff,
#                                      ExitStatus,
#                                      ExitSignal,
#                                      WindowAdjusted,
#                                      OpenFailure, Success,
#                                      Failure, RequestSuccess,
#                                      RequestFailure
#     • Typed `russh::Channel`         typed channel object
#                                      with typed `data()`,
#                                      `extended_data()`,
#                                      `eof()`,
#                                      `request_shell()`,
#                                      `request_pty()`,
#                                      `request_exec()`,
#                                      `request_subsystem()`,
#                                      `request_x11()`,
#                                      `request_env()`,
#                                      `request_signal()`,
#                                      `request_window_change()`,
#                                      `wait()` async operations
#     • Typed key-exchange algorithms  typed `kex` enum with
#                                      typed concrete: typed
#                                      curve25519-sha256 (RFC
#                                      8731), typed curve25519-
#                                      sha256@libssh.org, typed
#                                      ecdh-sha2-nistp256, typed
#                                      ecdh-sha2-nistp384, typed
#                                      ecdh-sha2-nistp521, typed
#                                      diffie-hellman-group14-
#                                      sha256, typed diffie-
#                                      hellman-group14-sha1,
#                                      typed diffie-hellman-
#                                      group16-sha512, typed
#                                      diffie-hellman-group18-
#                                      sha512, typed
#                                      sntrup761x25519-sha512
#                                      (post-quantum, RFC 9742),
#                                      typed mlkem768x25519-sha256
#                                      (post-quantum)
#     • Typed cipher algorithms        typed `cipher` enum with
#                                      typed concrete: typed
#                                      chacha20-poly1305@openssh.com,
#                                      typed aes256-gcm@openssh.com,
#                                      typed aes128-gcm@openssh.com,
#                                      typed aes256-ctr, typed
#                                      aes192-ctr, typed
#                                      aes128-ctr
#     • Typed MAC algorithms           typed `mac` enum with
#                                      typed concrete: typed
#                                      hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,
#                                      typed hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,
#                                      typed hmac-sha2-512,
#                                      typed hmac-sha2-256,
#                                      typed hmac-sha1
#                                      (deprecated but supported
#                                      for legacy)
#     • Typed compression              typed `zlib@openssh.com`
#                                      compressor
#     • Typed public-key auth         typed
#                                      `russh::keys::PrivateKey`
#                                      + typed
#                                      `russh::keys::PublicKey`
#                                      + concrete typed
#                                      ssh-ed25519, typed
#                                      ssh-ed25519-cert-v01@openssh.com,
#                                      typed ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,
#                                      typed ecdsa-sha2-nistp384,
#                                      typed ecdsa-sha2-nistp521,
#                                      typed rsa-sha2-256, typed
#                                      rsa-sha2-512, typed ssh-rsa
#                                      (legacy), typed
#                                      sk-ssh-ed25519@openssh.com
#                                      (FIDO2/WebAuthn-backed
#                                      hardware key), typed
#                                      sk-ecdsa-sha2-nistp256@openssh.com
#                                      (FIDO2/WebAuthn) ed25519
#                                      keys
#     • Typed agent forwarding         typed
#                                      `russh::keys::agent`
#                                      module with typed
#                                      `AgentClient` + typed
#                                      OpenSSH ssh-agent
#                                      protocol implementation
#     • Typed certificate auth         typed OpenSSH SSH
#                                      Certificate format
#                                      (`*-cert-v01@openssh.com`)
#                                      with typed `Certificate`
#                                      builder + verifier
#     • Typed known-hosts handling     typed `russh::known_hosts`
#                                      module with typed hashed-
#                                      hostname + plaintext-
#                                      hostname matching
#     • Typed direct-tcpip port-forward
#       (typed `Channel::open_direct_tcpip()`)
#     • Typed forwarded-tcpip remote
#       port-forward
#     • Typed direct-streamlocal Unix-
#       socket forward
#     • Typed forwarded-streamlocal remote
#       Unix-socket forward
#     • Typed X11 forwarding
#     • Typed shell + exec + subsystem
#       channel requests (the typed
#       interfaces used by every SCP /
#       SFTP / rsync-over-SSH /
#       devcontainer-CLI workflow)
#     • Typed PTY + window-change +
#       env + signal + xon-xoff requests
#     • Typed `russh-sftp`              separate typed crate
#                                      built on russh, exposing
#                                      typed SFTP server +
#                                      client primitives (the
#                                      SCP successor RFC-draft
#                                      file-transfer protocol)
#     • Typed `russh-keys`              separate typed crate for
#                                      typed PEM / OpenSSH /
#                                      PKCS#8 / PuTTY-PPK
#                                      private-key parsing +
#                                      typed encrypted-key
#                                      decryption (typed bcrypt-
#                                      kdf, typed PKCS#5 v2)
#     • Typed `russh-config`            separate typed crate
